readme:
Service Usage

This service allows a consumer to retrieve all visa application referrals details, as specified by the Visa Application ID, all the referrals included within it and notes history summaries.
This service also allows a consumer to retrieve a specific visa application referrals details, as specified by the Visa Application ID and Referral Id, and notes history details.
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a consumer wants to view the referrals information pertaining to a visa application.

Service Behaviour

A consumer of this service provides:
Unique identifier of the visa application and, optionally, a unique identifier of the referral
A consumer of this service receives either:
Data consisting of a subset of information from the following CDM Subject Areas:
o Party
o Referral
o Note

Or
An Enterprise Error detailing why the retrieve was unsuccessful.

Service Variants

This service has no service variants.

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer already having a unique identifier of a Visa Application as a Visa Application Id. The service also relies on the consumer providing the unique identifier of the referral when required for retrieving notes history details

Service Composition

This service is a composite service. It is composed of service SV176 (Transform Identifier) within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

The following service flow describes a successful execution path.
Service Consumer invokes service on ESB.
ESB transforms RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralRequest into ICSE XML and sends it to ICSE.
ICSE executes CICS transaction and returns ICSE XML to ESB.
ESB transforms ICSE XML into RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralResponse. (Enterprise Acknowledgement)
ESB check RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralResponse for the returned clientId(s) -then call SV176 (Transform Identifier) to retrieve the partyId(s) for this given clientId(s) and use the partyId(s) in the response.
ESB returns RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralResponse to Consumer.

1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider (ICSE) raises an error.

  1. Service Consumer invokes service on ESB.
  2. ESB transforms RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralRequest into ICSE XML and invokes service provider ICSE.
  3. ICSE executes CICS transaction and returns ICSE XML to ESB.
  4. ESB detects that ICSE has returned an error and constructs corresponding SOAP fault segment.
  5. ESB transforms ICSE Error into Enterprise Error Message.
  6. ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.

1.1.2 Alternate Flow 2
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the service SV176 raises an error.

  1. Service Consumer invokes service on ESB.
  2. ESB transforms RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralRequest into ICSE XML and sends it to ICSE.
  3. ICSE executes CICS transaction and returns ICSE XML to ESB.
  4. ESB transforms ICSE XML into RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralResponse. (Enterprise Acknowledgement)
  5. ESB check RetrieveVisaApplicationReferralResponse for the returned clientId -then call SV176 (Transform Identifier) to retrieve the partyId for this given clientId.
  6. ESB detects that SV176 has returned an error and constructs corresponding SOAP fault segment.
  7. ESB transforms SV176 Error into Enterprise Error Message.
  8. ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
